com.vector.cfg.model.groovy.api

Interface IMdfWriteApi

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ITransactionApi, ITransactionApiEntryPoint

    @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
 @PublishedApiDomain(value=AUTOMATION_IF)
public interface IMdfWriteApi
    The IMdfWriteApi API provides methods which allow modifying MDF model objects in different ways.
    The mdfWrite methods provide entry points to start navigation through the MDF model. Client code can use the Closure overloads to navigate into the content of the found MDF objects. Inside the called closure the related MDF object is available as closure parameter.

    The following types of entry points are provided here:

    • #mdfWrite(TypedAsrPath) searches an object with the specified AUTOSAR path
    • #mdfWrite(TypedDefRef) searches all objects with the specified definition

    This behavior is similar to mdfRead so far. But there are two differences:

    1. mdfWrite opens a transaction if there is no transaction opened yet (see chapter for details about transactions)
    2. When a member object doesn't exist during navigation into nested closures, it is being created automatically

      • mdfConfiguredWrite

        @PublishedMethod
<T extends com.vector.cfg.model.mdf.commoncore.autosar.MIReferrable> IMdfWriteSingleConfigurator<T> mdfConfiguredWrite(TypedAsrPath<T> asrPath)
        Returns a configuration object for the object found with the specified AUTOSAR path. This configurator provides means to configure the write mode.

        This method does not limit the search to the ActiveEcuC!

        Remark: Even in post-build selectable models this method expects to find at most one object because script code will never run in an unfiltered context.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the (expected) model object type
        Parameters:
        asrPath - an AUTOSAR path
        Returns:
        the writer configurator

      • mdfWrite

        @PublishedMethod
<T extends com.vector.cfg.model.mdf.commoncore.autosar.MIReferrable> T mdfWrite(TypedAsrPath<T> asrPath,
                                                                                                  @DelegatesTo(value=IMdfModelNavigator.class)
                                                                                                  groovy.lang.Closure<?> closure)
        Calls the closure for the object found with the specified AUTOSAR path and opens a transaction if there is no transaction open.

        This method does not limit the search to the ActiveEcuC, so it can be used to retrieve any object with this path.

        Remark: Even in post-build selectable models this method expects to find at most one object because script code will never run in an unfiltered context.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the (expected) model object type
        Parameters:
        asrPath - an AUTOSAR path
        closure - the code to execute
        Returns:
        The found object
